definitions.definition: To move, pass, or go forward or onward; to advance; to carry on
To pass from one point, topic, or stage, to another.
definitions.example: To proceed with a story or argument.

definitions.definition: To come from; to have as its source or origin.
To go on in an orderly or regulated manner; to begin and carry on a series of acts or measures; to act methodically
To be transacted; to take place; to occur.
(of a rule) To be applicable or effective; to be valid.
To begin and carry on a legal process.

definitions.example: They will donate all proceeds—the entire amount collected in ticket sales—from the show to charity.
They will donate net proceeds—whatever money is left after they pay their expenses—from the show to charity.
